A_415 - We are used to thinking of mud as a grey/brown liquid earth, but in reality the color can also be different from that and depends on the chemical and bacteriological composition of the soil. Obviously different types of soil have different impacts on the growth of plants and trees. In certain circumstances it can also be injected into the soil to carry out &ldquo;not too invasive&rdquo; fertilization and indeed in some cases it represents the absolute best solution available.